### 1. List All Users (Initially Empty)
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/users

### 2. Create User - Alice
POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice",
  "email": "alice@premix.io"
}

### 3. Create User - Bob
POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob",
  "email": "bob@premix.io"
}

### 4. List All Users (Should have 2)
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/users

### 5. Get User by ID (Alice = 0)
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/users/0

### 6. Get Non-existent User (Expect 404)
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/users/9999

### 7. Update User - Change Alice's Name
PUT http://127.0.0.1:3000/users/0
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Updated"
}

### 8. Verify Update (Get Alice Again)
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/users/0

### 9. Delete User - Bob (ID = 1)
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:3000/users/1

### 10. Verify Deletion (Expect 404)
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/users/1

### 11. List All Users After Delete (Should have 1)
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/users
